      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "From a strict natural rights viewpoint, any intervention is fundamentally suspect because it subordinates individual liberty to collective governmental authority. However, a nuanced defense often invokes the \"harm principle,\" suggesting regulation is only justifiable when speech directly incites imminent violence or causes demonstrable, substantial harm to others. Proponents of this limited view argue that the right to free expression ends where the rights of others begin.",
